{
  "texts": [
    "When the latter is triggered, realisations of σ2 N are typically smaller for NEnKF than SMC 2.",
    "Bayesian filtering for state-space models in the presence of unknown static parameters is a challenging problem.",
    "Sequential Monte Carlo algorithms must overcome particle degeneracy; one such scheme that deals with static parameters in a principled way is the SMC 2 scheme of Chopin et al. (2013).",
    "Here, parameter particles are weighted by an estimate of the current observed-data likelihood and, subject to some degeneracy criterion, mutated via a (pseudo-marginal) Metropolis-Hastings kernel which has the marginal parameter posterior as its invariant distrubution.",
    "A particle filter over the latent state process is used to estimate the required observed-data likelihood contributions."
  ]
}